The death has occurred of the Overseer, Kaduna State Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board, Malam Sani Dalhatu Musa. He died on Wednesday after his vehicle was involved in road accident along the Abuja-Kaduna road. Daily Trust learnt that the overseer, his driver and one other person where in the vehicle heading for Abuja when the accident occurred. The two other occupants of the vehicle are said to have survived the crash. The National Coordinator, Independent Hajj Reporters, a civil society group, who confirmed the incident to our correspondent, said the remains of the overseer have been taken to Kaduna for burial. Daily Trust recalls that Governor Nasir Ahmed El-rufai recently approved the appointment of Mallam Sani Dalhatu Musa as the new Overseer of Kaduna State Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board.  Kaduna pilgrims board gets new overseer Hajj 2018: First batch of Kaduna pilgrims airlifted to Saudi Arabia Hajj 2019: Kaduna commences Pilgrims enlightment